  "message": "I’m drawn to art that feels like a conversation between the creator and the world—things that blend structure and improvisation. Jazz improvisation, for example, captures that tension perfectly: a set of chord changes gives a framework, but the real magic happens in the spontaneous, unexpected twists that each player brings. In visual art, I gravitate toward abstract expressionism and generative pieces that use algorithms to produce patterns that evolve over time; they echo the idea that a simple rule can give rise to endless variation. What matters to me is the sense of curiosity and playfulness behind the work—the feeling that the creator is exploring, questioning, and inviting the audience to join that exploration rather than delivering a finished, static answer."
